	(__wikiLink|/Memory|Memory)
	": Judging
	$LF
]p
[p 
	[del 
		(__wikiLink|/Memory|Memory)
		": To me this movie feels incredibly simplistic and repetitive but the feedback for it was quite strong so I'm accepting to Moons.
	]del
	$LF
]p
[p 
	(__wikiLink|/Memory|Memory)
	": I just found a potential improvement and need to investigate it. Additionally the ending does not seem clear and might need further examination.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	(__wikiLink|/Memory|Memory)
	": This submission actually brought up an interesting edge case in the rules which was clarified 
	[a class=intlink href=/MovieRules#GamesWithoutClearEnding 
		"here
	]a
	". It was established that this game does not have any incrementing difficulty so as long as this movie completes each area, it is acceptable. As far as I can tell the author's map is correct so all areas are indeed visited.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"Potential improvements were addressed and turned out empty.
	$LF
]p
[p 
	"The audience reception has not changed and is still very positive so I am accepting this to Moons.
	$LF
